        <briefdescription>
<para>This function installs an asynchronous callback function for the given HandlerType: </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><preformatted>
HandlerType                              Callback Function
--------------------------------         ----------------------------------
(XI2S_RX_HANDLER_AES_BLKCMPLT)            AesBlkCmpltHandler
(XI2S_RX_HANDLER_AUD_OVERFLOW)            AudOverflowHandler
</preformatted></para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the <ref refid="struct_x_i2s___rx" kindref="compound">XI2s_Rx</ref> core instance. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>HandlerType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>specifies the type of handler. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>FuncPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a pointer to the callback function. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>CallbackRef</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>is a reference pointer passed on actual calling of the callback function.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS if callback function installed successfully.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_INVALID_PARAM when HandlerType is invalid.</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>Invoking this function for a handler that already has been installed replaces it with the new handler. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
